Prologue
"Please!" begged Queen Eirwen. "Don't send her away! She's just a child!" The Ice King looked down at his wife from his throne, his royal advisor standing beside him. She had given birth to a daughter. He frowned at the thought.
The little girl looked very much like her mother: pale blue eyes, white hair streaked with blue strands. The Ice King thought a daughter would make him look weak. After all, he had only had sons up until now.
"Your only options are to kill your child or send her into the wild. It's her punishment for your bad behavior, Eirwen." He spat out her name as if it were poison. He always did.
Frostwell was not always a single kingdom. It had been split into two, the North and the South. In the North, the non-magical kingdom. In the South, a kingdom filled with fantastical representations of power. Due to the greed of the North, the two kingdoms tore each other apart in an endless war, until the South proposed a truce.
The South was cornered, and its royal family would have done anything to stop the bloodshed. They proposed that their only princess become the queen of the North and bear a son destined to be the future king. Then, the South would have allied with the North to form a single kingdom. The North had accepted, and Princess Eirwen had married Prince Akull.
"I beg you, my highness, in exchange for my child's life, do with me as you wish, imprison me, banish me, or even, kill me," pleaded Queen Eirwen, holding her child tightly in her arms.
The Ice King looked down at his wife, disgust in his eyes. Perhaps, perhaps he might have pity for her. The one who had lived with him for twenty-two years, who had always taken care of him during his darkest hours, who had given birth to his sons.
"Very well, the child may live in the palace," he began, drawing a sigh of relief from his wife. "However," he added, "you will be executed."
The advisor and Queen Eirwen herself exchanged a horrified look. She slowly lowered her gaze. "Yes, my highness," she said, bowing her head.
The King of Frost commanded the royal advisor to take the child to one of Eirwen's empty chambers. Once this was done, he ordered the guards to lead Eirwen to the execution site, where all the villagers could witness the spectacle.
As the guards escorted her to the site, the villagers cried out in outrage upon seeing their only queen, the kindest, about to be killed. Some wept, others screamed and tried to attack the guards, while others questioned what was happening, but all were outraged.
"Free her!"
"Why are they doing this to her?"
As Eirwen approached the wooden gallows, the most feared person in the kingdom made his entrance. The user of fire. The former queen Eirwen was about to be burned alive. No one deserved such a death, not even criminals. It was the cruelest punishment in Frostfell.
Eirwen was attached to the gallows, and the king began to explain how the queen had betrayed all of them. The people of Frostfell refused to believe him and never accepted his words. Then, the user of fire burned the gallows, and a single tear rolled down the cheek of the ex-queen.
"Survive, Kari". This was the end of Queen Eirwen's reign.
Silence in the corridors
Tap, tap, tap. These were the only sounds coming from the farthest room on the left side of the always frozen south wing of the palace. The attendants passing by always wondered what was inside that room, afraid of what could be found within. The rumors of the maids danced through the corridors. It was believed that the late wife of the Ice King, Eirwen, was in that room, waiting to be freed.
"They could not be more mistaken," thought Ivory as she walked toward the south wing, while the attendants went back and forth whispering to each other. They don't know at all what is in that room.
